President and CEO of RBC Bearings Michael J. Hartnett Sells 29,000 Shares


July 10, 2012, 02:46:16 PM EDT
By GuruFocus, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo



RBC Bearings Incorporated (
  ROLL

  ) is an international manufacturer and marketer of highly
  engineered precision bearings and components. RBC Bearings
  Incorporated has a market cap of $1.05 billion; its shares were
  traded at around $47.64 with a P/E ratio of 21.3 and P/S ratio of
  2.7. RBC Bearings Incorporated had an annual average earnings
  growth of 3.3% over the past five years.
  


  On July 9, 2012, President and CEO of RBC Bearings Incorporated (
  ROLL

  ) Michael J. Hartnett sold 29,000 shares at an average price of
  $47.94. The total transaction amount is $1.4 million.
  


  Michael J. Hartnett has been the CEO and president of ROLL since
  April 1992 and chairman of the board since June 1993. Before
  coming to RBC Bearings, Hartnett was the president and general
  manager of the company's Industrial Tectonics Bearings Corp.
  subsidiary from 1990. After that, he worked at Torrington Company
  as vice president and general manager for 18 years.
  


  Michael J. Hartnett has also sold 68,724 shares of ROLL stock in
  June, May and July 3. Other directors and officers have also sold
  shares. Corporate Controller Thomas M. Burigo sold 1,000 shares
  of ROLL stock on May 30 at the average price $46.34. VP and
  General Manager Richard J. Edwards sold 12,500 and Director
  Richard R. Crowell sold 4,500 shares of ROLL stock on February
  23.
  


  GuruFocus Guru
  John Keeley

  has reduced his position in RBC Bearings Inc. As of March 31, he
  owns 515,600 shares of ROLL, a 21.59% decrease from the previous
  quarter.
  


  On May 30, 2012, RBC Bearings Incorporated reported their 2012
  fourth quarter fiscal results. The company reported net income of
  $15.5 million and net sales of $111.3 million.
  


  Read More:
  

John Keeley




